From 27990fccac83c96c72dd5082054c2c90c7c2831b Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: emergent-agent-e1 <github@emergent.sh>
Date: Fri, 10 Jul 2026 09:30:10 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] fix(deploy): replace MongoDB with Supabase, fix backend
 startup crash

The Python backend crashed on startup because supa.py reads
SUPABASE_URL/SUPABASE_SECRET_KEY at import time (hard KeyError), but the
.env template written by setup.sh only contained MONGO_URL/DB_NAME.
The systemd unit also had Requires=mongod.service, which prevented the
backend from starting on hosts without MongoDB, and the mongodb-org 7.0
apt block failed on Ubuntu 24.04 (noble) due to missing packages.

deploy/setup.sh:
- Remove the MongoDB 7 install block entirely (unused at runtime).
- Rewrite the .env template with all vars the backend requires:
  SUPABASE_URL, SUPABASE_SECRET_KEY, SUPABASE_DB_URL, LIVEKIT_URL,
  LIVEKIT_API_KEY, LIVEKIT_API_SECRET (corrected from _KEY suffix),
  OPENAI_API_KEY, STRIPE_API_KEY, JWT_SECRET, FIXED_ADMIN_*.
- Migrate legacy Mongo-only .env files by appending the Supabase block.
- Run scripts/init_supabase.py (best-effort schema apply).
- Drop Requires=mongod.service from the systemd unit.
- Pre-flight: refuse to start with placeholder secrets.
- Post-start /api/health smoke test with journalctl dump on failure.

deploy/redeploy.sh:
- Add /api/health smoke test + log dump + exit 1 on failure.

deploy/README.md:
- Replace MongoDB instructions with Supabase (creds, schema apply,
  scaling), add upgrade-from-Mongo section.
